message.body: Omg! I LOVE the myth of Sisyphus
By Camus or do you mean the Greek myth? Where are you based?
The myth of Sisyphus who was punished by the gods by having to push a boulder up a hill only to have it roll back down... I'm just south of Philadelphia... You?
Right on. i'm down in north FL, geting pounded by tropical storm Andrea @ the moment. What do you do in PA?
I'm a copy editor... What do you do? How did you hear about this study?
I used to live in west philly, was a semi-pro guinea pig, so i did all kind of crazy stuff like this.
I do electrical work for money. For joy i do all manner of activities involving water, love paddling & scuba. I also enjoy travel & am pretty civicly-engaged.
Cool... I'm a homebody.. Like reading, crafting and I volunteer with a no-kill cat shelter.
Nice. Save the kitties!
I have 2 of my own cats... Do you have any pets?
I have a beautiful, elderly cat that i'm caretaking for a friend. Definitely an adorer of felines!
Cool. I have a chihuahua too but he lives with my parents.. He didn't like being separated from his brother and sister
Do you enjoy living in the philly area? You from there?
I live in the house I grew up in... I bought it 5 years ago... The neighborhood is changing and I'd like to move away but it's difficult being single andonly bringing in one salary, you know?
Totally. I'm in the same boat. No real desire to partner up with anyone, but man it would be nice to have a 2nd income, or at least a sugar mamma!
I'm actually in the process of trying to buy my grandma's house.
Yeah... I was trying to hit that 600 million powerball.. Can't believe an 84 year old hit
Funny, thats the town where my folks live, zephyrhills. I called my mom on the way to work that morning just to make sure i still had to go in! No luck!
Hmmm, maybe that 84 year old is looking for a house boy!
Haha.. Good luck
